            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="exhibition"></a>Public exhibition of plans for a new care home. Friday 11th October</a></h3>
                <p>To be held in All Saints small hall, Onslow Gardens, CR2 9AB. Friday 11th October, 3 - 7 pm.</p>
                <p>Churchgate services are putting on a public exhibition for a chance to find out more about their proposals to build a new 60 bed care home on the corner of Sanderstead Hill and Addington Road.</p>
                <p>Churchgate services is primarily focussed across the south of England where they have developed a range of sites including residential and commercial, although care homes are the main focus of the group. They want to hear from local residents - come to the public exhibition to hear more.</p>
                <p>If you can't come to the exhibition they still want to hear your views. Contact josephb@curtinandco.com, tel 0207 399 2294</p>
              </td>
              <td class="events">
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="Quiz"></a>Sanderstead Nieighbourhood Care Quiz Night. Saturday 12th October</h3>
                <p>NOW FULLY BOOKED</p>
                <p>Sat 12 October, 7 pm for a 7.30pm start. Tickets: £10 per person. Payment in advance only! 6 people per table. Ticket price includes a ploughman’s & dessert but please bring your own glasses and drink. Any special dietary requirements
                need to be advised in advance. There will be a raffle on the night</p>
                <p>All Saints Church Hall, Onslow Gardens, Sanderstead CR2 9AB</p>
                <p>Book tickets by calling 020 8657 8289, come into the office or email. sandersteadneighbourhoodcare@gmail.com</p>
              </td>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><%= link_to "SNC", "resource/snc_quiz2019.pdf" %></h3>
              </td>
          </tr>

          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="boot"></a>Charity Boot Sale. Saturday 12th October</h3>
              <p>St Paul's Church's Autumn Boot Sale will take place on Saturday 12th October at St Paul’s Church Hall, Croham Park Avenue, South Croydon from 9.30 am until 12.30 pm.</p>
              <p>There will be 30 or more stalls selling a variety of pre-owned goods including clothing and shoes, books and games, toys, bric a brac, collectables and much more at bargain prices.</p>
              <p>Admission is 50 pence and accompanied children under 14 are admitted free of charge. Early bird admission is from 9.00 am and costs 2 Pounds.</p>
              <p>Sellers need to pre-book tables by contacting the Organiser on 01883 723081 or by email (tinkerscorner@aol.com).</p>
              <p>We have been running boot sales at St Paul’s for almost 20 years and have
              attracted a loyal following. All proceeds go to supporting youth work in the area including Scouts, Brownies and Junior Church and amongst other things we also make donations towards sending shoe boxes to Eastern Europe.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events"><h3><%= link_to "St Paul's", "https://www.stpaulsurc.org.uk/" %></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

